The paper deals with distributed computing tasks under fault-tolerant contexts and communication constraints, which are typical topics in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also focuses on clock synchronization and consensus problems, which are fundamental topics in the Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of self-stabilizing algorithms is another key aspect of the paper, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of small message sizes, which is a topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
